The paper focuses on the use of additional contact points to enhance the robustness and manipulation capabilities of quadrupedal robots. This falls under the field of robotics, specifically in the area of robot locomotion and manipulation. Therefore, cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a hierarchical quadratic programming based whole-body controller, which involves optimization and control theory, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also involves computation of the Smallest Unrejectable Force (SUF), which is related to Feasible Wrench Polytopes, indicating a possible connection to computational geometry and optimization, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) possible sub-categories as well.
